botLot.pathFinding.Algorithms

Class BotLotPFAlgorithm

  • java.lang.Object
    • botLot.pathFinding.Algorithms.BotLotPFAlgorithm
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BotLotPFDijkstra, BotLotPFRandom

    public abstract class BotLotPFAlgorithm
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstract class to set up the methods needed for all path generation.

      • calculatePath

        protected abstract LotPath calculatePath()
                                  throws BotLotPFAlgException
        Put the actual path finding code here, already checked for object readiness.

        DO NOT CALL THIS FROM ANY OTHER CLASS THAN THE SUB CLASS YOU IMPLEMENTED THIS IN

        Only reason this is not a private method is because abstract methods can't be private.

        Returns:
        A path from the curNode to the destNode through the graph.
        Throws:
        BotLotPFAlgException - If something goes wrong in path finding.
